Best vegan options I've ever had. The delicious spicy "buffalo wings" and whipped coconut cream with blueberries spring to mind. I recommend this place to anyone who appreciates a good kosher vegetarian meal besides falafel. Also really enjoyed the surprising, creative  salad of goat feta (this one was dairy :)) with fresh herbs and slightly exotic lettuces (expertly checked to be bug-free, of course), and fruit that i didn't expect to go so well. They have a bar and a nice selection of wine. Our own waiter was helpful, but the others who weren't assigned to us were unnecessarily snobby and unfriendly. But this was a year and a half ago, and that's something that can really change fast, especially with the turnover in that job.

Don't bother going if you are not jewish! I am jewish my husband is not and does not wear a yarmulke. We've eaten here on numerous occasions because of a certain dish we enjoy tremendously and brought many guests as well. We are fed up with the constant rushing of our meals, the stares to see if we've finished the appetizers we are eating to the point of embarrassment in front of guests when the main course arrives while still having the appetizers and the cludder of dishes on the table.  We are always treated differently from the other yarmulke adorned people. The constant staring to see when the check can be delivered. Tonite we walked in and took our usual seats at a table in the back that happens to be a table for 4. With at least 4 tables for 4 empty and an hour before closing  we were very rudely told we could not sit there but had to sit on the 2 seat side, which we find too small and uncomfortable. I said I can't imagine that many people could rush in to eat in the hour that the restaurant would remain open. We were treated in an EXTREMELY crude manner, got up and left. Absolutely no attempt was made by the manager to inquire what was wrong. He just stood there and watched us leave, knowing full well what was wrong because he sent the waiter to move us and he knows us as well as where we like to sit. Unbelievable!!!
